# GRIND-TOTAL equivalents for blocked_commands.py — see equivalents-security-core.md
# (Category B* sections). Each entry below is a mutant proven GENUINELY
# EQUIVALENT by hand: apply the exact cosmic-ray mutant -> full suite stays
# green -> revert. Listed here it is excluded from the kill-rate denominator.
# A mutant is listed ONLY if no honest input can distinguish it from the
# original for ANY reachable input.
#
# IDENTITY FORMAT (re-init-proof): each entry is the mutant's STABLE identity
#   operator_name|start_row:start_col-end_row:end_col|occurrence
# NOT a job_id. cosmic-ray regenerates job_ids on every `init`, so job_id-keyed
# skips silently match nothing after a re-init (the false-100% trap). The
# harness (tests/evals/mutkill_approval_grants.py: stable_id/compute_skip_jobids)
# resolves these stable ids to the current session's job_ids and WARNS on any
# token that matches no mutant. Re-keyed against blocked-commands.sqlite
# (157 specs, post-desacople HEAD).
#
# Endpoint: every blocked_commands.py survivor is either killed by a test in
# tests/hooks/modules/security/test_blocked_commands_mutants.py OR proven
# equivalent here. Confirmed 0 untriaged survivors via mutkill --skip-file.
#
# ===========================================================================
# Category B1 — _has_unquoted_separator quote-walk equivalents (19)
# Invariant: i advances by 1 or 2 and the escape branch is gated by i+1<n, so
# i lands EXACTLY on n (never overshoots). See equivalents-security-core.md B1.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# B1a loop bound `while i < n` (line 705): != / is-not equivalent
#   (i reaches n exactly; for short reachable commands `is not` coincides with
#   `!=` and both coincide with `<` at the n boundary).
core/ReplaceComparisonOperator_Lt_IsNot|705:12-705:13|0
core/ReplaceComparisonOperator_Lt_NotEq|705:12-705:13|0
# B1b escape guard `if ch == "\\" and i + 1 < n` (line 707)
#   Eq_Is on ch (single-char interning: command[i] for "\\" is identity-equal)
core/ReplaceComparisonOperator_Eq_Is|707:14-707:16|2
#   Add_* on i+1 (Sub/Mul/Div/FloorDiv/Mod/Pow/RShift/BitOr/BitAnd/BitXor):
#   only observable when ch=="\\"; every reachable backslash command keeps i
#   landing on n, so the guard truth-value is unchanged. Add_LShift was KILLED
#   (aaaa\|) so it is NOT listed here.
core/ReplaceBinaryOperator_Add_BitAnd|707:28-707:29|1
core/ReplaceBinaryOperator_Add_BitOr|707:28-707:29|1
core/ReplaceBinaryOperator_Add_BitXor|707:28-707:29|1
core/ReplaceBinaryOperator_Add_Div|707:28-707:29|1
core/ReplaceBinaryOperator_Add_FloorDiv|707:28-707:29|1
core/ReplaceBinaryOperator_Add_Mod|707:28-707:29|1
core/ReplaceBinaryOperator_Add_Mul|707:28-707:29|1
core/ReplaceBinaryOperator_Add_Pow|707:28-707:29|1
core/ReplaceBinaryOperator_Add_RShift|707:28-707:29|1
core/ReplaceBinaryOperator_Add_Sub|707:28-707:29|1
#   NumberReplacer 1->0 on i+1 (occ5); occ4 1->2 was KILLED
core/NumberReplacer|707:30-707:31|5
#   Lt_* on `i + 1 < n` (NotEq / LtE / IsNot)
core/ReplaceComparisonOperator_Lt_IsNot|707:32-707:33|1
core/ReplaceComparisonOperator_Lt_LtE|707:32-707:33|1
core/ReplaceComparisonOperator_Lt_NotEq|707:32-707:33|1
# B1c quote-toggle Eq_Is (single-char interning) lines 710, 714
core/ReplaceComparisonOperator_Eq_Is|710:14-710:16|3
core/ReplaceComparisonOperator_Eq_Is|714:14-714:16|4
# ===========================================================================
# Category B2 — is_blocked_command empty-guard or->and (line 596)
# Diverges only for whitespace-only inputs; both yield is_blocked=False
# (the `and` branch falls through, strips to "", and the pattern loop matches
# nothing -> same observable).
core/ReplaceOrWithAnd|596:19-596:21|1
# ===========================================================================
# Category B3 — _read_only_base_cmds unreachable except ImportError (line 74)
# The sibling import always succeeds in-process; the handler body never runs.
core/ExceptionReplacer|74:11-74:22|0
